# What is a Method?

Structs don't just hold data (Properties). They can also hold their own **Functions**! When a function lives inside a Struct, it is called a **Method**.

Let's give our Player the ability to introduce themself!

```swift
struct Player {
    var name: String
    var score: Int

    func introduce() {
        print("Hi, I'm \(name)! My score is \(score).")
    }
}
```

